<doc id="1229417" wikidata="Q3414003" url="?curid=1229417" title="Queen Elizabeth (band)">
<text>Queen Elizabeth are a British band. It is a collaborative experimental project between Thighpaulsandra and Julian Cope. The general concept behind Queen Elizabeth was a &quot;sonic ritual&quot; in which sounds, melodies and other sonic properties would combine. Both releases, 1994&#x27;s &quot;Queen Elizabeth&quot; and 1997&#x27;s double-disc &quot;Queen Elizabeth 2: Elizabeth Vagina&quot;, consist mostly of half-hour-long tracks which contrast experimental ambient music with short bursts of Krautrock. The three discs (and seven tracks) are the band&#x27;s only studio output, yet &quot;Beneath the Frozen Lake of Stars&quot;, which appeared on Thighpaulsandra&#x27;s &quot;I, Thighpaulsandra&quot;, was a revamped version of a track destined for a third Queen Elizabeth release. Cope has said that Thighpaulsandra&#x27;s version went above and beyond the original recording they made together.

In 2009, a recording of the band&#x27;s only live performance in May 2000 was released as an mp3 download entitled &quot;Hall&quot; through Cope&#x27;s official website.

==Discography==
*&quot;Queen Elizabeth&quot; – (1994)
*&quot;Queen Elizabeth 2: Elizabeth Vagina&quot; – (1997)
*&quot;Hall&quot; – (2009)

